          <li><strong>Lead Generation:</strong> <a href="https://get.apollo.io/fxnpnadnv4lb" rel="sponsored nofollow">Apollo.io</a> for finding commercial prospects and building targeted lead lists ($49/user/month)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="buying-decision">Making Your FieldEdge Decision</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>FieldEdge makes sense if you:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Have 10+ technicians and complex operations</li>
          <li>Need extensive customization and reporting</li>
          <li>Have budget for $400-600+ monthly software costs</li>
          <li>Require advanced inventory management features</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Consider alternatives if you:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Have fewer than 10 technicians</li>
          <li>Want to minimize setup time and costs</li>
          <li>Prefer month-to-month contracts over annual commitments</li>
          <li>Need simple, reliable field service management</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Final Recommendation</h3>
        <p>FieldEdge delivers solid functionality but at premium pricing. For most small to medium HVAC companies, <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/vcuhehgs796s" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a> or <a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">Housecall Pro</a> provide better value with faster implementation and lower total costs.</p>

        <p>Only choose FieldEdge if you need its specific advanced features and have the budget to pay 40-60% more than alternatives. For guidance on the best fit for your company, read our comprehensive <a href="/hvac/guides/how-to-choose-hvac-software">HVAC software selection guide</a>.</p>
